***import numpy as np*** - importing numpy library - allows us to create numpy arrays
(arrays that can contain values of only one datatype)
np.array([...])

***math methods***
name.shape
name.arange()
name.zeros()
np.full()
np.full()

***converting python lists to numpy arrays***
np.array(list)

***slicing numpy arrays***
name[start:end:steps]

***slicing 2d numpy arrays***
name[start:end:step, start:end:step]

***numpy universal function***
np.sqrt()
np.absolute()
np.exp()
np.max()
np.min()
np.sign(
np.sin()
np.log()

***copy and view of the numpy array***
name.view()
name.copy()

****shape and reshape numpy arrays***
name.shape
name.reshape()

***iterating through numpy arrays***
for x in name: ...
np.nditer()

***sorting numpy arrays***
np.sort()

***searching through numpy arrays***
np.where()

***filtering numpy arrays***
x = [True, False, True...]
filtered.append()
filtered = ... 
